The paper deals with the problem of estimating aggregates over multiple weight assignments, which is a common problem in databases and data analysis. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a sampling framework and obtains estimators, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the empirical evaluation of the proposed methods, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
